<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,781,918]" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,785,810]" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">Remarks.</emphasis>
Both the 
<typeStatus box="[376,435,786,810]" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">types</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[503,586,785,810]" name="Bolivia" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
are similarly colored to 
<taxonomicName box="[859,1012,785,810]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Tomaspisinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callangana">
<emphasis box="[859,1012,785,810]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">T. callangana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1183,1235,786,809]" name="Peru" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[1249,1334,781,810]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="36" pageNumber="237" precision="925" value="-12.566667">12o34'S</geoCoordinate>
76o19W, the type-locality also for 
<taxonomicName box="[437,628,821,846]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Tomaspisinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteomaculata">
<emphasis box="[437,628,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">Z. luteomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The senior name is based on a male slightly larger (8.5.mm) than the two female 
<typeStatus box="[288,347,858,882]" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">types</typeStatus>
(
<quantity box="[365,487,857,882]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="36" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="7.75" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.5">7.5–8 mm</quantity>
). It will take considerably more specimens and/or barcoding to validate additional species where morphological characters are so indefinite.
</paragraph>
